Do not call the method [create(java.io.File file)][5] instead of [create(java.io.InputStream inp)][4] while using `WorkbookFactory` and creating your `Workbook`, it will lead to problems when saving your file as it&#39;s discussed on [this post][6].

I really don&#39;t know the reason why you initially add the tag &quot;selenium&quot; to your question *but* if you&#39;re thinking to use some spider-code to &quot;manually&quot; open and edit your excel file, please don&#39;t. This solution is as horrible as HSSF is (did you get the [joke][7]?).

