The problem with your current approach is that your regular expression is not specific enough to match only the values you want. Instead, it is matching any sequence of one or more word characters, followed by either a comma, a comma and a space, or another word character, followed by either a comma or the end of the string.

A more specific approach would be to use the following regular expression:

&quot;(\bvalue\d+\b)(,\s)*&quot;

This will match any sequence of the word &quot;value&quot; followed by one or more digits and a comma and a space.

You can use it like this:

    Pattern p = Pattern.compile(&quot;(\\bvalue\\d+\\b)(,\\s)*&quot;);
    Matcher m = p.matcher(jfield);
    while (m.find()) {
        System.out.print(m.group(1) + &quot; &quot;);
    }

